<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-36-1315 </DOCNO><TEXT>Growth of the magnetic fluctuations due to the m = 1 and m = 2 modes,where m is the poloidal mode number, and succeeding phase-lock of thesemodes have been found as the precursor phenomena of the rapid destructionof the plasma column (current termination) in reversed field pinch (RFP).By deepening the field reversal at the wall, these precursors disappear,and the plasma current duration becomes much longer. Thus the currenttermination is closely connected with the growth of MHD instabilitieswith the m = 1 and m = 2 modes.</TEXT></DOC>